President Donald J. Trump has provided a supplemental consolidated report to Congress, as required by the War Powers Resolution, on the deployments of U.S. Armed Forces equipped for combat. The report outlines the military operations in support of United States counterterrorism efforts, including deployments to various countries such as Afghanistan, Iraq, Syria, Yemen, Jordan, Turkey, East Africa, Djibouti, Libya, and the Lake Chad Basin region. The report also mentions military operations related to the Lord's Resistance Army, military operations in Syria and Egypt, and the security of United States citizens and property in South Sudan. The President states that these operations are carried out to protect U.S. citizens and interests and are authorized by his constitutional and statutory authority as Commander in Chief and Chief Executive.